9:
Always is! The bazaar has been like this 
ever since I was little.
16:
Yes, I used to visit the bazaar on the 
way home from my clergical training. 
It feels so long ago, now.
19:
How about we take a stroll around 
after we finish our errands?
26:
It IS awfully crowded though. I'm a little 
worried we'll get split up if we aren't 
careful.
29:
I know! Alk, would you give me your 
hand for a second, please?
36:
Thank you. We won't get separated 
now!
41:
W-wait, you were asking to hold my 
hand?!
I thought you were going to do 
something magic-y... What if people 
think we're, um, y'know?
45:
This is a clergical technique known as 
the Guiding Hand.
51:
Even when clouds obscure our vision, 
the Stars continue to shine. However, 
some have trouble believing in that 
which they cannot see.
52:
And so, it is the duty of those the Light 
reaches to take the lost by the hand, 
and be the Beacon which guides them.
54:
The Guiding Hand is one of the first 
things the Bishop taught me—and for 
good reason! It always comes in 
handy.
57:
R-right... I bet you were the type of kid 
who'd wander off if an adult wasn't 
keeping hold of you.
60:
Hm? How could you tell?
...In any case, this is my home town. 
You don't have to worry about getting 
lost as long as I'm here to guide you!
64:
I'm less worried about getting lost and 
more worried about getting seen. Your 
fanclub wouldn't like th—WHOA! Liesel, 
wait!
73:
Is it? F-finally...
I thought I was done for. I don't know if 
I could've lasted another minute!
78:
Oh no, what's wrong? You should have 
told me you weren't feeling well. I'll fix 
you right up, don't you worry!
83:
I'm fine! I'm fine, but boy that was 
stressful. I've never been glared at like 
that in my life!
86: Hmm? Well, I'm glad you're okay!
90:
I've finally found you!
You're coming with me, missy!
93: What do you want with Liesel?
96: Who is this riff-raff? Stay out of this!
98:
Look, I don't know who you are, but 
I won't let you do anything to my 
friend!
104:
EEP?! WHAT'S THAT?! 
LOOK BEHIND YOU!
112: I—*wheeze*—I think this is far enough.
126:
Oh, no, no it's just—ahaha—the look on 
Dad's face!
136:
Sorry, I know I should have said 
something, but you whisked me away 
before I had a chance. Goodness, that 
was hilarious!
140:
I'm so sorry, Liesel. I'll go back and 
apologize right away!
143:
No, it's fine, really. I'm sure he was just 
trying to drag me home.
146:
Not too long ago, you were out on the 
streets, and now you're living all the 
way in Starview. I'm sure your Dad 
must be—
150:
Wait, wait, hold on! Why were you 
living on the streets?! Your Dad had 
butlers with him!
153:
Why, because I ran away from home, 
of course. I'm a bit of a delinquent!
155:
He's much too protective of me, and 
was very against my charity work in 
the Kaleidoscope. While I AM quite 
sorry to worry him like this...
158: You have no intentions to stop.
167:
So much for our stroll around the 
bazaar. I'm sorry, Liesel.
170:
That's all right. I had plenty of fun 
walking around doing the groceries 
with you!
173:
Really? As long as you had fun, that's 
what counts.
175:
Well, should we start heading back to 
Starview?
